    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Hanover County was formed from New Kent County in 1720.
</p>
      <p>Most county court records, particularly deeds, wills, and marriage records, were destroyed by fire in Richmond on 3 April 1865, where they had been moved for safekeeping during the Civil War. The circuit court records were not moved to Richmond and were relatively unscathed. Consequently, there is a strong run of common law papers and chancery papers after 1831 that were generated by the circuit superior court of law and chancery and its successor, the circuit court.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Hanover County (Va.) Clerk's Fee Bills, 1788-1793.
Consists of two bills for court fees issued by Hanover County Clerk William Pollard.</p>
    </scopecontent>
